## Approach
HTTP client targeting Claude 4.6+-class via Anthropic's tool-use API. Implements ModelProvider from .14. tool_use content blocks ŌåÆ ModelDecision. Vision via image content blocks (base64 PNG). Hosts the SHARED frontier helpers (FrontierDefaults, VisionImage, validateToolArgs, lookupTool) that .37 consumes ŌĆö that is why .37 depends on .36. Web-compatible HTTP only.

## Constraints
- Web-compatible (PRD ┬¦22): no dart:io. HTTP via `package:http`.
- Frontier defaults (PRD ┬¦16.4): lower temp, smaller obs budget, tighter retries vs MLX.
- Capability metadata: vision per-model (Claude Sonnet/Opus 4.6+); preserveThinking false.
- Schema validation reuses .14's `ActionSchema`.

## Ruled out
- `anthropic_sdk_dart`: opaque around capability/schema hooks.
- Combining .36 + .37 in one bead: blew 12KB during compression ŌĆö distinct response shapes don't dedup.

## Non-obvious notes
- Anthropic tool names match `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]{1,64}$`. ToolDescriptor.name is dotted (`core.tap`). encode/decode swaps `.` Ōåö `_`.
- `thinking()` returns `Stream.empty()` here; .23 extends with streaming later.
- Provider throws SchemaRejection; the loop driver (.18) is the retry-once owner per .14's contract.

