## Approach
HTTP client targeting GPT-5-class via OpenAI Chat Completions tools[] API. Implements `ModelProvider` (.14). `tool_calls[]` (`function.name` + JSON-string `function.arguments`) ŌåÆ `ModelDecision`. Reuses shared frontier helpers (`FrontierDefaults`, `VisionImage`, `validateToolArgs`, `lookupTool`) from .36. Vision via `image_url` parts. Schema-rejection retry-once. Web-compatible HTTP only.

## Constraints
- Web-compatible per PRD ┬¦22 ŌĆö no dart:io. HTTP via `package:http`.
- Frontier-tier defaults reused from .36.
- vision=per-model; preserveThinking has no OpenAI equivalent.
- Schema validation reuses .14's `ActionSchema`.

## Ruled out
- `openai_dart` package: thin HTTP layer keeps capability + schema hooks under our control.
- Sharing parser code with .36: tool_use blocks vs tool_calls don't dedup cleanly.

## Non-obvious notes
- Strictly depends on .36 for shared helpers (per .36's `## Touches`); do NOT duplicate.
- .18 (loop driver) depends on .36 AND .37 ŌĆö convergence point.
- Streaming variant feeds DevTools thinking panel (.23).
- Pin to modern `tools[]`/`tool_calls[]`, not deprecated `functions[]`.

