## Approach
Reference plugin in `packages/exploration_router/` against the v1 contract from `package:exploration_flutter/contract.dart` (lenny-cx6.3). Holds a `GlobalKey<NavigatorState>` (imperative) and an optional `RouterDelegate<Object>` (declarative); `observe()` reads imperative first, declarative as fallback (mixed-app rule). Single tool `navigate` (bare name; merged key `router.navigate`) calls `NavigatorState.pushNamed`. `busyState()` always `BusyState.idle` ŌĆö routing transitions ride the host's frame stability signal (lenny-cx6.4). `initialize`/`dispose`/`onActionExecuted` are no-ops. Per-plugin 1024-byte serialized observation cap (PRD ┬¦11.4); oversize fragments emit `'_truncated': true`.

## Constraints
- Uses contract symbols `ExplorationPlugin`, `ExplorationTool`, `ToolResult`, `BusyState`, `JsonSchema`, `ObservationContext`, `ExecutedAction`, `PluginContext`.
- Tool's bare `name` is `navigate`; merged tool key is `router.navigate`.
- Per-plugin observation budget = 1024 bytes; oversize ŌåÆ fragment with `'_truncated': true`.

## Ruled out
- `go_router`/`auto_route`/`beamer` adapters (v0.5 chose raw primitives).
- Pushing `MaterialPageRoute` directly: named routes only.
- `busyState` contributions (validated by lenny-cx6.27).
- Lifecycle hooks beyond `initialize`/`dispose`.

