## Approach
Thinking sub-panel as a scrollable monospace view that consumes a `Stream<TurnEvent>` from the active `ExplorationSession`. Provider .14 exposes `Stream<ThinkingDelta>` from `thinking()`; loop driver .18 forwards each delta plus action+validation events to `session.emitTurnEvent()` without buffering. Panel widget subscribes, appends to an `AppendOnlyTextController` (version-counter `ValueNotifier`), renders inside a single `ValueListenableBuilder`. After action+validation per turn, two trailing lines are appended. Auto-scroll follows bottom; manual scroll-up pauses; "Jump to live" affordance resumes.

## Constraints
- Streaming end-to-end (no buffer-then-emit) per PRD ┬¦23.
- Append must not rebuild the parent tree per token ŌĆö leaf `ValueListenableBuilder` only.
- Web-compat: no `dart:io` (PRD ┬¦22).
- Manual scroll-up must reliably pause auto-scroll; resumes only on explicit user tap.

## Ruled out
- Out-of-process token channel (in-panel session shares state directly per PRD ┬¦6.3).
- Buffer-full-trace-per-turn (defeats v0.5 KEY USER VALUE).
- Markdown rendering (deferred ŌĆö plain monospace v1).

## Non-obvious notes
- The per-turn `TurnEvent` stream is shared infrastructure with the timeline panel (.24); both consume it.
- Subscription lifecycle is kept clean for the .31 mid-turn-interrupt follow-up.

