## Approach
Single-column Flutter form rendered into .21's Prompt tab placeholder: goal `TextField`, model `DropdownButton` (from providers wired in .14/.15/.16), turn-count + wall-clock budget inputs (PRD ┬¦10 defaults), `CheckboxListTile` group for plugin enablement, `Start` button. Plugin toggles come from the .11 binding handshake (registered namespaces), all enabled by default; zero plugins ŌåÆ empty-state hint to plugin authoring guide (.35). Start collects state into a `PromptPanelConfig`, instantiates `ExplorationSession` in-panel via a `PromptPanelController`, disables form inputs while running, and replaces Start with Stop. Stop calls `session.end()` and is wired so .31 can layer mid-turn interrupt extensions on the controller without restructuring.

## Constraints
- Plugin list comes only from the live handshake (.11), never a static config. Empty list renders the guide-hint, not a stub.
- Form must be `enabled: false` / `onChanged: null` while running, not just visually dimmed.
- Stop wiring lives on `PromptPanelController` (extensible), not inlined into the widget.
- Web-only (no `dart:io`) inherited from .21.
- Model dropdown reflects only providers passed in via `availableModels`; no hardcoded ids in the widget file.

## Ruled out
- Replicating CLI argument parsing (PRD ┬¦6.3 ŌĆö advanced flags stay CLI-only).
- Multi-step wizard ŌĆö single-page form fits the iterative dev pattern.
- Persisting form state across DevTools sessions ŌĆö not v1.

## Non-obvious notes
- Bead's only declared dep is .21 (scaffold); .11 already exposes `HandshakeResult`/`PluginManifestEntry`/`ExplorationSession.start/end/progress`/`ExplorationConfig`.
- This panel realizes PRD ┬¦23's "usable prompt-and-watch loop within 30 seconds" entry point.
- `PromptPanelConfig` is a value class with `==`/`hashCode` so .31 can extend without restructuring.

